PROJECT: VelocityCore — Forge 1.20.1 server+client optimization mod.

CONTEXT:
- Minecraft Forge 1.20.1, mappings: official 1.20.1, Forge 47.3.0, Java 17
- Mixin 0.8.5 via SpongePowered (built into Forge 1.20.x)
- Server-side systems: Dist.DEDICATED_SERVER on all event subscribers
- Client systems: Dist.CLIENT only, in the client/ package
- Primary compatibility targets: William Wythers Expanded Ecosphere (WWEE), Chunky Forge

ARCHITECTURE:
- 15 systems total. Each system is one Java class in system/ or client/
- All systems are individually toggleable via VCConfig boolean fields
- ServerTickHandler drives all server systems via TickEvent.ServerTickEvent
- ClientTickHandler drives client systems via TickEvent.ClientTickEvent
- ChunkGenThrottle is the single shared budget — all gen work checks hasBudget() before proceeding

SYSTEM MAP:
  S1  ChunkGenThrottle         — system/ChunkGenThrottle.java
  S2  SmartChunkCache          — system/SmartChunkCache.java
  S3  DeferredDecorator        — system/DeferredDecorator.java
  S4  EntityActivationManager  — system/EntityActivationManager.java
  S5  SpawnRateLimiter         — system/SpawnRateLimiter.java
  S6  PreLoadRing              — system/PreLoadRing.java
  S7  SmartEviction            — system/SmartEviction.java
  S8  ChunkStatusFastPath      — system/ChunkStatusFastPath.java
  S9  RegionFileBuffer         — system/RegionFileBuffer.java
  S10 ModdedMobNormalizer      — system/ModdedMobNormalizer.java
  S11 MobCapGuard              — system/MobCapGuard.java
  S12 PathfindingThrottle      — system/PathfindingThrottle.java
  S13 ChunkPacketPrioritizer   — client/ChunkPacketPrioritizer.java
  S14 VelocityHintSender       — client/VelocityHintSender.java
  S15 ClientEntityCuller       — client/ClientEntityCuller.java

MIXIN MAP:
  MixinServerChunkCache           → net.minecraft.server.level.ServerChunkCache
  MixinNoiseBasedChunkGenerator   → net.minecraft.world.level.levelgen.NoiseBasedChunkGenerator
  MixinNaturalSpawner             → net.minecraft.world.level.NaturalSpawner
  MixinMob                        → net.minecraft.world.entity.Mob
  MixinPathFinder                 → net.minecraft.world.entity.ai.navigation.PathFinder

THREAD SAFETY:
- NEVER write block state or LevelChunk data off the main server thread
- Decoration draining (DeferredDecorator) ONLY runs inside ServerTickEvent on main thread
- SmartChunkCache uses ThreadLocal — one map per worldgen thread, zero shared mutable state
- RegionFileBuffer uses a separate I/O thread for warming only — never writes world data

MIXIN RULES:
- All mixin targets are vanilla classes — never mixin directly into WWEE classes
- Always use @Inject with CallbackInfo, prefer @At("HEAD") with cancellable=true
- Never use @Overwrite
- Add a comment above every @Inject explaining why this injection point was chosen
- Mixin class names always prefix with Mixin (MixinServerChunkCache etc)

CHUNKY COMPATIBILITY:
- VelocityCore NEVER generates chunks inside the world border
- Before any PreLoadRing ticket is issued, verify ChunkStatus on disk == "full" via NBT tag
- If status is not full, fall back to DeferredDecorator — never issue a speculative ticket
- Read world border bounds from WorldBorder object at runtime — never hardcode radius

MODDED MOB RULES:
- ModdedMobNormalizer runs ONCE at server start after all mods finish registration
- It scans every biome's MobSpawnSettings and normalizes weights to range [5, 80]
- Formula: weight = clamp(weight * (vanillaBaseline / actualPoolTotal), 5, 80)
- It writes a full adjustment report to the server log
- VCConfig.MOB_NORMALIZER_EXEMPTIONS allows per-mod opt-out

CODE STYLE:
- Mojmap names for all MC classes
- No reflection unless unavoidable — prefer Mixin @Accessor
- Javadoc on every public method
- System.nanoTime() for timing always — never System.currentTimeMillis()
- All config keys snake_case, all Java identifiers camelCase
- When a system is disabled via VCConfig, it must be a complete no-op with zero overhead

CONFIG REFERENCE (all keys in config/velocitycore-server.toml unless noted):
  enable_tps_tracking         = true   (master TPS loop toggle)
  enable_gen_throttle         = true   (S1)
  enable_noise_cache          = true   (S2)
  noise_cache_size            = 4096   (S2, entries per worldgen thread)
  enable_deferred_decorator   = true   (S3)
  decoration_per_tick         = 4      (S3, 1-20)
  enable_preload_ring         = true   (S6, requires Chunky)
  enable_smart_eviction       = true   (S7)
  hot_chunk_max               = 512    (S7)
  enable_fast_path            = true   (S8)
  enable_region_buffer        = true   (S9)
  enable_ai_throttle          = true   (S4)
  enable_spawn_limiter        = true   (S5)
  enable_mob_normalizer       = true   (S10)
  mob_normalizer_max_weight   = 80     (S10)
  mob_normalizer_min_weight   = 5      (S10)
  mob_normalizer_exemptions   = []     (S10, list of mod IDs)
  enable_mob_cap_guard        = true   (S11)
  enable_pathfinding_throttle = true   (S12)
  enable_chunk_prioritizer    = true   (S13, client toml)
  enable_velocity_hint        = true   (S14, client toml)
  enable_entity_culler        = true   (S15, client toml)
  entity_cull_range           = 64     (S15, blocks)

BUILD ORDER FOR CURSOR PROMPTS:
  01 VCConfig + VCNetworkChannel           (config first — every system references it)
  02 ChunkGenThrottle + ServerTickHandler  (heartbeat — verify with /velocitycore status)
  03 ServerTickHandler wiring              (already covered in 02)
  04 SpawnRateLimiter + MixinNaturalSpawner
  05 EntityActivationManager + MixinMob
  06 ModdedMobNormalizer
  07 MobCapGuard + PathfindingThrottle + MixinPathFinder
  08 DeferredDecorator + SmartChunkCache + MixinNoiseBasedChunkGenerator
  09 PreLoadRing + SmartEviction + RegionFileBuffer
  10 ChunkStatusFastPath + MixinServerChunkCache
  11-15 Client jar: ChunkPacketPrioritizer + VelocityHintSender + ClientEntityCuller
